      • hasRelationship

        boolean hasRelationship(long sourceConceptId,
                        long destinationConceptId,
                        long relationshipTypeId)
        Checks whether a relationship with the given relationship type exists between the two SNOMED CT concept. Returns true if a relationship between the source and destination concepts given by their unique ID exists. Otherwise returns with false.
        Parameters:
        sourceConceptId - the source concept ID.
        destinationConceptId - the destination concept ID.
        relationshipTypeId - the relation type concept ID.
        Returns:
        return true, if there is a relationship between the two concepts, otherwise returns with false.
